# Clayforge вЂ” Complete Deployment Guide
## From zero to live in ~45 minutes

---

## WHAT YOU'LL SET UP
1. Supabase (PostgreSQL database вЂ” free)
2. Railway (backend API hosting вЂ” free tier)
3. Vercel (frontend hosting вЂ” free)
4. Stripe (USD payments)
5. Paystack (NGN payments)

---

## STEP 1 вЂ” DATABASE (Supabase)
**Time: ~5 minutes | Cost: Free**

1. Go to https://supabase.com and click "Start your project"
2. Sign up with GitHub (easiest)
3. Click "New Project"
   - Name: `clayforge`
   - Password: choose a strong password (save it!)
   - Region: choose closest to Nigeria (e.g. EU West or US East)
4. Wait ~2 minutes for database to spin up
5. Go to Settings в†’ Database
6. Copy the "Connection string" (URI format)
   - It looks like: `postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.xxxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres`
   - Replace `[YOUR-PASSWORD]` with the password you chose
7. **Save this string** вЂ” you'll need it in Step 2

---

## STEP 2 вЂ” BACKEND (Railway)
**Time: ~10 minutes | Cost: Free ($5 credit monthly)**

1. Go to https://railway.app and sign up with GitHub
2. Click "New Project" в†’ "Deploy from GitHub repo"
3. Connect your GitHub account and push the `backend/` folder as a repo
   - Or: Click "Empty Project" в†’ "Add a Service" в†’ "GitHub Repo"
4. Once deployed, click your service в†’ "Variables" tab
5. Add these environment variables one by one:

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.xxxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres
JWT_SECRET=paste-a-random-64-character-string-here
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app    (update after Step 3)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxx               (from Step 4)
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx            (from Step 4)
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxx            (from Step 5)
PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_xxx            (from Step 5)
PORT=3001
```

6. After setting DATABASE_URL, go to the "Deploy" tab and run:
   ```
   npm run db:generate && npm run db:push
   ```
   (This creates all the database tables automatically)

7. Copy your Railway URL (e.g. `https://clayforge-backend.up.railway.app`)
   в†’ You'll need this for the frontend

---

## STEP 3 вЂ” FRONTEND (Vercel)
**Time: ~5 minutes | Cost: Free**

1. Go to https://vercel.com and sign up with GitHub
2. Push the `frontend/` folder to a GitHub repo
3. Click "Add New Project" в†’ import your frontend repo
4. In "Environment Variables" add:
   ```
   VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.up.railway.app
   VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_xxx
   ```
5. Click "Deploy"
6. Your app will be live at e.g. `https://clayforge.vercel.app`

7. **Go back to Railway** and update `FRONTEND_URL` to your Vercel URL

---

## STEP 4 вЂ” STRIPE (USD Payments)
**Time: ~10 minutes**

1. Go to https://stripe.com and create an account
2. Complete business verification (takes 1-2 days for live mode)
3. For testing first, use test mode keys

**Get your API keys:**
- Dashboard в†’ Developers в†’ API Keys
- Copy `Secret key` (sk_live_... or sk_test_...)
- Add to Railway as `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`

**Set up webhook:**
- Dashboard в†’ Developers в†’ Webhooks в†’ "Add endpoint"
- URL: `https://your-backend.up.railway.app/api/webhooks/stripe`
- Events to select:
  - `customer.subscription.created`
  - `customer.subscription.updated`
  - `customer.subscription.deleted`
- Copy the "Signing secret" в†’ add to Railway as `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`

**Create Customer Portal (for subscription management):**
- Dashboard в†’ Settings в†’ Billing в†’ Customer Portal
- Enable it and save

---

## STEP 5 вЂ” PAYSTACK (NGN Payments)
**Time: ~5 minutes**

1. Go to https://paystack.com and create a business account
2. Verify your business (CAC registration or BVN for individuals)
3. Dashboard в†’ Settings в†’ API Keys & Webhooks
4. Copy:
   - Secret key в†’ Railway `PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY`
   - Public key в†’ Railway `PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY` AND Vercel `VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY`

**Set webhook URL:**
- Settings в†’ API Keys & Webhooks в†’ Webhook URL
- Enter: `https://your-backend.up.railway.app/api/webhooks/paystack`
  (Note: Paystack webhook handler can be added later вЂ” Paystack payments
   are verified synchronously in the app, so subscriptions activate immediately)

---

## STEP 6 вЂ” CONNECT EVERYTHING
After all steps, update these values:

**In Railway (backend env vars):**
```
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-actual-vercel-url.vercel.app
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
```

**In Vercel (frontend env vars):**
```
VITE_API_URL=https://your-actual-railway-url.up.railway.app
VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_...
```

Redeploy both after updating variables.

